littleAboutUsText:
Unlike the .html() method, .text() can be used in both XML and HTML documents.
 The result of the .text() method is a string containing the combined text of all
 matched elements. (Due to variations in the HTML parsers in different browsers,
  the text returned may vary in newlines and other white space.)
